Benakat, Bumi Minerals, Medco Energi: Indonesia Equity Preview

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-03-04T01:54:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-04/benakat-bumi-minerals-medco-energi-indonesia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and share prices are as of the previous close.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  rose 0.2 percent to 3,494.54.  Energy companies: Crude oil is headed for its third weekly
gain in  New York  with the April delivery contract rising 0.3
percent to $102.17 a barrel in after-hours trading.  PT Energi Mega Persada (ENRG IJ), Indonesia’s second-
biggest listed oil company, gaining 1.8 percent to 112 rupiah.
PT Benakat Petroleum Energy (BIPI IJ) was unchanged at 87
rupiah.  PT Bumi Resources Minerals (BRMS IJ): The mining unit of
Indonesia’s biggest coal producer, PT Bumi Resources (BUMI IJ),
obtained $143 million in dividends from owning a stake in PT
Newmont Nusa Tenggara and will use the proceeds to repay debt,
Kontan reported without saying where it obtained the
information. Bumi Minerals gained 1.5 percent to 660 rupiah and
Bumi advanced 4.2 percent to 3,075 rupiah.  PT Medco Energi Internasional (MEDC IJ):  Indonesia ’s
biggest listed oil company has allocated $275 million to develop
its Area 47 block in  Libya  and expects the block to start
producing in mid-2014, Investor Daily Indonesia reported, citing
Director Lukman Mahfoedz. Medco was unchanged at 2,900 rupiah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
 bmoestafa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at   dboey@bloomberg.net  